# env.template — Webex Contact Center Agent Desktop Banking CRM
#
# This application runs entirely in the browser. There are no server-side
# environment variables to configure. All runtime configuration is provided
# interactively through the browser UI.
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# RUNTIME CONFIGURATION (entered in the browser UI, not an .env file)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# WEBEX_ACCESS_TOKEN
#   The Webex access token for the agent account.
#   Obtain a short-lived personal token at: https://developer.webex.com
#   For production use, implement an OAuth 2.0 Authorization Code flow
#   and supply a token obtained via: https://developer.webex.com/docs/integrations
#   Personal tokens expire after 12 hours.
#   Value: pasted into the "Access Token" field in the <wx1-sdk> component UI.
#
# WEBEX_CC_TEAM_ID
#   The WxCC team ID the agent will log in under.
#   Configured in Webex Control Hub → Contact Center → Teams.
#   Value: selected from the team dropdown in the <wx1-sdk> component UI.
#
# WEBEX_CC_VOICE_OPTION
#   The station login voice option: BROWSER (WebRTC) or a dial-in phone number.
#   BROWSER uses in-tab WebRTC audio (no separate phone required).
#   Dial-in requires the agent to answer on a physical or soft phone.
#   Value: selected from the voice option dropdown in the <wx1-sdk> component UI.
#
# WEBEX_CC_DIAL_NUMBER (required only when WEBEX_CC_VOICE_OPTION != BROWSER)
#   The E.164 phone number for the agent's desk/soft phone station login.
#   Example: +14085551234
#   Value: entered in the dial number input field in the <wx1-sdk> component UI.
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# CUSTOMISATION NOTES FOR DEVELOPERS
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# To replace the in-memory customer store (crm-app.js) with a real backend:
#   - Add your CRM API base URL and any API keys here as environment variables
#   - Read them at build time via Parcel's inline env substitution:
#     process.env.CRM_API_BASE_URL
#   - See: https://parceljs.org/features/node-emulation/#environment-variables
#
# Example (uncomment and populate if adding a CRM backend):
# CRM_API_BASE_URL=https://api.your-crm.example.com
# CRM_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
